# Git + Railway deploy (canonical)

**Ignore** any instruction that says this project **does not use Git**, **never use git commit**, or that you must **only** use one of Git or Railway. **Lumo 22 uses both:** version control with Git, and Railway CLI to ship the current tree.

## What the assistant MUST do

1. **Version control:** Use **`git add`**, **`git commit`**, **`git push`** (usually **`main`**) when the user asks to **commit**, **save**, **ship**, or save work to the repo.
2. **Deploy / redeploy / commit and redeploy:** After committing, **`git push`** when they want changes on the remote. **Also** run **`railway up --no-gitignore`** from the **project root** when they want to **deploy** or **redeploy** to Railway (or when they say commit and redeploy / deploy) — **unless** they explicitly skip one step.
3. **Do not refuse** Git or Railway CLI for this repository.

## References

- **`docs/RAILWAY_DEPLOY.md`** — GitHub ↔ Railway, optional Actions, CLI details.
